KW  - austerity
KW  - debt limit
KW  - fiscal limit
KW  - solvency crisis
KW  - default
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0022-2879
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/jmcb.13034
Y2  - 2024/10/27
N2  - Abstract Many high-debt countries are adopting tax austerity, whereby governments raise the tax rate as their debt levels rise with the hope to dispel future solvency crises. This paper investigates the impact of tax austerity on government debt solvency. A solvency crisis occurs once adverse shocks push the debt above its effective debt limit, the maximum level of debt that the government can repay. I show that the position of the effective debt limit depends on tax austerity. I find that high-debt countries like Italy that undergo tax austerity could lower their effective debt limit and induce a solvency crisis.
ER  - 

